38 "§ 160D-605. Governing board statement.
39 (a) Plan Consistency. – When adopting or rejecting any zoning text or map amendment,
40 the governing board shall approve a brief statement describing whether its action is consistent or
41 inconsistent with an adopted comprehensive or land-use plan. The requirement for a plan
42 consistency statement may also be met by a clear indication in the minutes of the governing board
43 that at the time of action on the amendment the governing board was aware of and considered
44 the planning board's recommendations and any relevant portions of an adopted comprehensive
45 or land-use plan. If a zoning map amendment is adopted and the action was deemed inconsistent
46 with the adopted plan, the zoning amendment has the effect of also amending any future land-use
47 map in the approved plan, and no additional request or application for a plan amendment is
48 required. A plan amendment and a zoning amendment may be considered concurrently. The plan
49 consistency statement is not subject to judicial review. If a zoning map amendment qualifies as
50 a "large-scale rezoning" under G.S. 160D-602(b), the governing board statement describing plan
